SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 704
By Reeves
A RESOLUTION to honor Chris Garrett, 2026 President of
Tennessee REALTORS.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in paying tribute
to those exemplary professionals who have ascended to the very pinnacle of their chosen
professions; and
WHEREAS, Chris Garrett is currently serving as President of Tennessee REALTORS, a
station that reflects and rewards his many years of dedication to and excellence in Tennessee's
real estate industry; and
WHEREAS, as 2026 President of Tennessee REALTORS, Mr. Garrett continues to
champion professionalism, advocacy, and member engagement statewide; and
WHEREAS, Chris Garrett is deeply passionate about teaching, mentoring, and
developing real estate professionals, investing his time and energy into helping others succeed;
and
WHEREAS, Mr. Garrett is a man of faith, and his values are evident in both his
leadership style and his personal conduct, guiding his decisions with integrity, humility, and
purpose; and
WHEREAS, Chris Garrett began his distinguished career in real estate in late 2005; he
currently serves as broker and co-owner of Weichert Realtors–The Andrews Group in
Murfreesboro; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Garrett is widely regarded as a dedicated and principled leader whose
enthusiasm and commitment to expertise inspire those he serves; and
WHEREAS, throughout his career, he has demonstrated a "lead from the front"
approach to leadership, earning the respect of colleagues across the industry; and
SJR0704
012711
- 1 -

WHEREAS, a Golden R President's Circle Hall of Fame RPAC Investor, Chris Garrett
exemplifies a steadfast commitment to protecting private property rights and advancing the real
estate profession's voice at every level of government; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his current leadership role, he previously served as President
of the Middle Tennessee Association of REALTORS and 2014-2015 Division 2 Vice President
for Tennessee REALTORS; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of his exceptional leadership, service, and impact on the
profession, Chris Garrett was honored as Tennessee's REALTOR of the Year in 2021; and
WHEREAS, a dedicated public servant in many areas, Mr. Garrett was a reserve deputy
with the Rutherford County Sheriff's Office for four years; he has been recognized as a subject
matter expert for the National Association of REALTORS Safety Matters course, and he serves
as federal political coordinator for U.S. Congressman Scott DesJarlais; and
WHEREAS, his many professional achievements aside, Chris Garrett is most
appreciative of the love and companionship he shares with his wife, Carrie, and their two
children; and
WHEREAS, Chris Garrett continues to inspire his peers with his unwavering
commitment to the REALTOR mission and his community, and he is richly deserving of our
approbation on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Chris Garrett for his service
as 2026 President of Tennessee REALTORS, extending our best wishes for much continued
success in all his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
